Open the terminal / command prompt and run:

node -v


If it shows a version number like v18.17.0, Node.js is already installed.
If not, download and install it from https://nodejs.org
 (choose the LTS version).

âš™ï¸ Step 2: Install SASS globally using npm

Once Node.js is installed, run this command in the terminal (not inside Node):

npm install -g sass


npm = Node Package Manager

-g = installs globally so you can use sass command anywhere

This downloads and installs SASS on your system.

